metadata.name: Key Gompa (Key Monastery)
metadata.description:
Spiti Valley's greatest Buddhist study centre, Key Monastery, dates back over a thousand years. It is one among the oldest training centres for Lama. Located in northern India's Himachal Pradesh region of Lahaul Spiti, it rises 13,668 feet above sea level. This image was captured using a DJI Inspire 2 and ultra wide lens Laowa 9mm f/2.8 Zero-D on X7 Gimbal.  A very unique image shot from the drone. 
You can get a very high resolution image as a signed art print that can be shipped anywhere in the world.
